    "narrative": "The centerpiece of today\u2019s lineup is undoubtedly **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 81.88. Facing Meider Kelly, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a substantial park boost (+16%) and a favorable platoon matchup, but the true differentiator is the projection of Kelly's slow delivery, which projects a massive 87% success rate for stolen base attempts, directly addressing our need for speed. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** also presents a strong play (70.49) against Martin Keller due to a favorable platoon split and a top-two lineup spot, the combination of **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s lead-off spot and high-upside speed dynamics makes him the primary engine for the Austin Waves today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.06) out of the starting nine. He was evaluated closely against the likes of **Drake Baldwin** and **Heliot Ramos**, but he ultimately lost out due to a negative park adjustment and a 11% reduction in projected efficiency against the starting pitcher, Misiorowski. We continue to prioritize efficiency scores in this 5x5 format, and while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** possesses an excellent xwOBA of .384, the raw projection favored the platoon advantages of our active starters. We are also monitoring a 39% rain risk for **Miguel Vargas**, though his 57.38 efficiency score and leadoff status keep him firmly in the lineup unless weather developments necessitate a late-inning pivot.\n\nConversely, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Luis Robert Jr.** (44.07) and **Andy Pages** (46.34). **Luis Robert Jr.** is facing the elite Yoshinobu Yamamoto, and while wind blowing out provides a marginal boost, his efficiency is cannibalized by a 16% negative adjustment for the opposing SP's skill and a poor platoon split. Similarly, **Andy Pages** is riding a 19% downgrade against the opposing arm, making him a high-risk start. If the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Kyle Tucker** or **Jacob Wilson** shifts unexpectedly, we will look to rotate in **Nasim Nunez**, who remains a high-value contingency option due to his speed upside against Keller\u2019s slow delivery.",
